{
  "doc_id": "45482",
  "text": "A total of 31 patients with a new diagnosis of RR-MS according to the 2010 revised McDonald criteria [CITATION_1] were consecutively recruited. They underwent clinical assessment, brain MRI, lumbar puncture (LP), ophthalmological assessment, and OCT at baseline. For each recruited patient, the Expanded Disability Status Scale (EDSS) score was assessed at baseline. An age-and sex-matched control group of healthy subjects was also recruited and underwent the same ophthalmological assessment.",
